The Quad countries (Australia, India, Japan, and the United States) have affirmed that technology should be designed, developed, governed, and used in a way that aligns with democratic values and respects universal human rights. They believe that technology should improve the lives of citizens by addressing global challenges such as equitable growth, climate change, energy security, and pandemic diseases. The Quad countries are committed to creating an open, accessible, and secure technology ecosystem based on mutual trust and confidence. They invite all nations to support the principles of supporting universal values, building trust and resilience, fostering healthy competition and international collaboration, and advancing the frontier of science and technology.